1 (h) a member of the clergy, as defined in 15-6-201(2)(b);
2 (i) a guardian ad litem or a court-appointed advocate who is authorized to investigate a report of
3 alleged abuse or neglect;
4 (j) an employee of an entity that contracts with the department to provide direct services to
5 children; and
6 (k) an employee of the department while in conduct of the employee's duties.
7 (3) A professional listed in subsection (2)(a) or (2)(b) involved in the delivery or care of an infant
8 shall report to the department any infant known to the professional to be affected by a dangerous drug, as
9 defined in 50-32-101.
10 (4) Any person may make a report under this section if the person knows or has reasonable cause
11 to suspect that a child is abused or neglected. The department shall follow the provisions of 41-3-212 when
12 taking the report.
13 (5) (a) When a professional or official required to report under subsection (2) makes a report, the
14 department:
15 (i) may share information with:
16 (A) that professional or official; or
17 (B) other individuals with whom the professional or official works in an official capacity if the
18 individuals are part of a team that responds to matters involving the child or the person about whom the report
19 was made and the professional or official has asked that the information be shared with the individuals; and
20 (ii) shall share information with the individuals listed in subsections (5)(a)(i)(A) and (5)(a)(i)(B) on
21 specific request. Information shared pursuant to this subsection (5)(a)(ii) may be limited to the outcome of the
22 investigation and any subsequent action that will be taken on behalf of the child who is the subject of the report.
23 (b) The department may provide information in accordance with 41-3-202(8) and also share
24 information about the investigation, limited to its outcome and any subsequent action that will be taken on
25 behalf of the child who is the subject of the report.
26 (c) Individuals who receive information pursuant to this subsection (5) shall maintain the
27 confidentiality of the information as required by 41-3-205.
28 (6) (a) Except as provided in subsection (6)(b) or (6)(c), a A person listed in subsection (2) may not
